\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 Architecture & Key Innovation\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\fs24 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Architecture
\f1\b0 : 130M-parameter GPT-2-style decoder-only transformer (causal LM)[{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://aclanthology.org/2025.babylm-main.41/"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 aclanthology}}]\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Training Objective
\f1\b0 : 
\f0\b Multi-Token Prediction (MTP)
\f1\b0  \'97 instead of predicting only the next token, trains the model to predict the next 
\f5\i k
\f1\i0  tokens simultaneously using multiple parallel output heads sharing a single backbone[{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://aclanthology.org/2025.babylm-main.41/"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 aclanthology}}]\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Key Innovation
\f1\b0 : 
\f0\b Forward Curriculum MTP
\f1\b0  \'97 a curriculum strategy that 
\f5\i gradually increases
\f1\i0  the number of predicted tokens (k) over training. Starts with standard NTP (k=1) in early epochs, then progressively adds more future-token prediction heads. This overcomes the known instability of MTP in small models[{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://aclanthology.org/2025.babylm-main.41/"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 aclanthology}}]\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Vocabulary Size
\f1\b0 : 16k tokens[{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://aclanthology.org/2025.babylm-main.41.pdf"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 aclanthology}}]\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Token Mixer
\f1\b0 : Standard self-attention[{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://aclanthology.org/2025.babylm-main.41/"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 aclanthology}}]\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

