\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 Architecture Matters for Fine-Tuning\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 There's an important structural consideration:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Encoder-only models
\f1\b0  (DeBERTa-V2, LTG-BERT, ELC-BERT) tend to fine-tune better on classification tasks because they see the full bidirectional context. AMLM (Edman) benefits massively from this \'97 achieving 70.7% GLUE avg.\
\ls7\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Decoder-only models
\f1\b0  (GPT-2-style, BLaLM, MTP) are fine-tuned by adding a classification head on top, which is slightly less natural for tasks like NLI but still works well.\
\ls7\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Hybrid encoder-decoder models
\f1\b0  (GPT-BERT) offer both causal and masked inference paths, and the masked path is typically used for fine-tuning.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 The leaderboard's 
\f0\b Text Average
\f1\b0  metric deliberately 
\f0\b excludes fine-tuning GLUE
\f1\b0  from the primary ranking (it uses the zero-shot composite), but GLUE is displayed as a separate column and was a significant factor in the findings paper's analysis of which approaches generalise best.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf6 \strokec6 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 Key Takeaway\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Fine-tuning is not incidental to BabyLM \'97 it's a first-class evaluation target. The leaderboard shows both:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls8\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Zero-shot Text Average
\f1\b0  (primary ranking metric)\
\ls8\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 (Super)GLUE fine-tuned score
\f1\b0  (secondary column, same weight in the paper's analysis)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Models like AMLM (Edman & Fraser) specifically designed their training objective to improve GLUE performance and achieved the best fine-tuning results in the entire Strict-Small track, even though their zero-shot scores were more modest \'97 which is an interesting tension in the challenge's dual-objective evaluation design.\
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
